  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between Right Bank and Left Bank Bordeaux Merlot?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Right Bank Bordeaux Merlot (from Pomerol and Saint-Émilion) grows in clay and limestone soils, producing wines with softer tannins, rich plum flavors, and elegant earthiness. Left Bank Merlot serves as a blending component with Cabernet Sauvignon in gravelly soils, creating more structured wines with cassis notes and firmer tannins. Right Bank Merlot is typically more approachable young, while Left Bank blends require more aging.</p>
  </div>

